OL,7,FBut the British Medical Association
OL,8,Fwarned the proposed changes could mean
OL,9,Ftransgender and non-binary patients
OL,10,Fcould "potentially find their access
OL,11,Fto vital NHS services limited", while
OL,12,Fthe Royal College of Nursing said
OL,13,Fchanges to health policy should be
OL,14,Fdone with patients "not unto them".
OL,16,FThe changes will also enshrine
OL,17,FMartha's Rule in the NHS Constitution
OL,18,Fin a bid to bolster patient safety.
